## SidebarProvider\par
\par
The `SidebarProvider` component is used to provide the sidebar context to the `Sidebar` component. You should always wrap your application in a `SidebarProvider` component.\par
\par
### Props\par
\par
| Name           | Type                      | Description                                  |\par
| -------------- | ------------------------- | -------------------------------------------- |\par
| `defaultOpen`  | `boolean`                 | Default open state of the sidebar.           |\par
| `open`         | `boolean`                 | Open state of the sidebar (controlled).      |\par
| `onOpenChange` | `(open: boolean) => void` | Sets open state of the sidebar (controlled). |\par
\par
### Width\par
\par
If you have a single sidebar in your application, you can use the `SIDEBAR_WIDTH` and `SIDEBAR_WIDTH_MOBILE` variables in `sidebar.tsx` to set the width of the sidebar.\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers title="components/ui/sidebar.tsx"\par
const SIDEBAR_WIDTH = "16rem"\par
const SIDEBAR_WIDTH_MOBILE = "18rem"\par
```\par
\par
For multiple sidebars in your application, you can use the `--sidebar-width` and `--sidebar-width-mobile` CSS variables in the `style` prop.\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers\par
<SidebarProvider\par
  style=\{\par
    \{\par
      "--sidebar-width": "20rem",\par
      "--sidebar-width-mobile": "20rem",\par
    \} as React.CSSProperties\par
  \}\par
>\par
  <Sidebar />\par
</SidebarProvider>\par
```\par
\par
### Keyboard Shortcut\par
\par
To trigger the sidebar, you use the `cmd+b` keyboard shortcut on Mac and `ctrl+b` on Windows.\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers title="components/ui/sidebar.tsx"\par
const SIDEBAR_KEYBOARD_SHORTCUT = "b"\par
```\par
\par
## Sidebar\par
\par
The main `Sidebar` component used to render a collapsible sidebar.\par
\par
### Props\par
\par
| Property      | Type                              | Description                       |\par
| ------------- | --------------------------------- | --------------------------------- |\par
| `side`        | `left` or `right`                 | The side of the sidebar.          |\par
| `variant`     | `sidebar`, `floating`, or `inset` | The variant of the sidebar.       |\par
| `collapsible` | `offcanvas`, `icon`, or `none`    | Collapsible state of the sidebar. |\par
\par
| Prop        | Description                                                  |\par
| ----------- | ------------------------------------------------------------ |\par
| `offcanvas` | A collapsible sidebar that slides in from the left or right. |\par
| `icon`      | A sidebar that collapses to icons.                           |\par
| `none`      | A non-collapsible sidebar.                                   |\par
\par
<Callout>\par
  **Note:** If you use the `inset` variant, remember to wrap your main content\par
  in a `SidebarInset` component.\par
</Callout>\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers\par
<SidebarProvider>\par
  <Sidebar variant="inset" />\par
  <SidebarInset>\par
    <main>\{children\}</main>\par
  </SidebarInset>\par
</SidebarProvider>\par
```\par
\par
## useSidebar\par
\par
The `useSidebar` hook is used to control the sidebar.\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers\par
import \{ useSidebar \} from "@/components/ui/sidebar"\par
\par
export function AppSidebar() \{\par
  const \{\par
    state,\par
    open,\par
    setOpen,\par
    openMobile,\par
    setOpenMobile,\par
    isMobile,\par
    toggleSidebar,\par
  \} = useSidebar()\par
\}\par
```\par
\par
| Property        | Type                      | Description                                   |\par
| --------------- | ------------------------- | --------------------------------------------- |\par
| `state`         | `expanded` or `collapsed` | The current state of the sidebar.             |\par
| `open`          | `boolean`                 | Whether the sidebar is open.                  |\par
| `setOpen`       | `(open: boolean) => void` | Sets the open state of the sidebar.           |\par
| `openMobile`    | `boolean`                 | Whether the sidebar is open on mobile.        |\par
| `setOpenMobile` | `(open: boolean) => void` | Sets the open state of the sidebar on mobile. |\par
| `isMobile`      | `boolean`                 | Whether the sidebar is on mobile.             |\par
| `toggleSidebar` | `() => void`              | Toggles the sidebar. Desktop and mobile.      |\par
\par
## SidebarHeader\par
\par
Use the `SidebarHeader` component to add a sticky header to the sidebar.\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers title="components/app-sidebar.tsx"\par
<Sidebar>\par
  <SidebarHeader>\par
    <SidebarMenu>\par
      <SidebarMenuItem>\par
        <DropdownMenu>\par
          <DropdownMenuTrigger asChild>\par
            <SidebarMenuButton>\par
              Select Workspace\par
              <ChevronDown className="ml-auto" />\par
            </SidebarMenuButton>\par
          </DropdownMenuTrigger>\par
          <DropdownMenuContent className="w-[--radix-popper-anchor-width]">\par
            <DropdownMenuItem>\par
              <span>Acme Inc</span>\par
            </DropdownMenuItem>\par
          </DropdownMenuContent>\par
        </DropdownMenu>\par
      </SidebarMenuItem>\par
    </SidebarMenu>\par
  </SidebarHeader>\par
</Sidebar>\par
```\par
\par
## SidebarFooter\par
\par
Use the `SidebarFooter` component to add a sticky footer to the sidebar.\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers\par
<Sidebar>\par
  <SidebarFooter>\par
    <SidebarMenu>\par
      <SidebarMenuItem>\par
        <SidebarMenuButton>\par
          <User2 /> Username\par
        </SidebarMenuButton>\par
      </SidebarMenuItem>\par
    </SidebarMenu>\par
  </SidebarFooter>\par
</Sidebar>\par
```\par
\par
## SidebarContent\par
\par
The `SidebarContent` component is used to wrap the content of the sidebar. This is where you add your `SidebarGroup` components. It is scrollable.\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers\par
<Sidebar>\par
  <SidebarContent>\par
    <SidebarGroup />\par
    <SidebarGroup />\par
  </SidebarContent>\par
</Sidebar>\par
```\par
\par
## SidebarGroup\par
\par
Use the `SidebarGroup` component to create a section within the sidebar.\par
\par
A `SidebarGroup` has a `SidebarGroupLabel`, a `SidebarGroupContent` and an optional `SidebarGroupAction`.\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers\par
<SidebarGroup>\par
  <SidebarGroupLabel>Application</SidebarGroupLabel>\par
  <SidebarGroupAction>\par
    <Plus /> <span className="sr-only">Add Project</span>\par
  </SidebarGroupAction>\par
  <SidebarGroupContent></SidebarGroupContent>\par
</SidebarGroup>\par
```\par
\par
To make a `SidebarGroup` collapsible, wrap it in a `Collapsible`.\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers\par
<Collapsible defaultOpen className="group/collapsible">\par
  <SidebarGroup>\par
    <SidebarGroupLabel asChild>\par
      <CollapsibleTrigger>\par
        Help\par
        <ChevronDown className="ml-auto transition-transform group-data-[state=open]/collapsible:rotate-180" />\par
      </CollapsibleTrigger>\par
    </SidebarGroupLabel>\par
    <CollapsibleContent>\par
      <SidebarGroupContent />\par
    </CollapsibleContent>\par
  </SidebarGroup>\par
</Collapsible>\par
```\par
\par
## SidebarMenu\par
\par
The `SidebarMenu` component is used for building a menu within a `SidebarGroup`.\par
\par
<Image\par
  src="/images/sidebar-menu.png"\par
  width="716"\par
  height="420"\par
  alt="Sidebar Menu"\par
  className="mt-6 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-lg border dark:hidden"\par
/>\par
<Image\par
  src="/images/sidebar-menu-dark.png"\par
  width="716"\par
  height="420"\par
  alt="Sidebar Menu"\par
  className="mt-6 hidden w-full overflow-hidden rounded-lg border dark:block"\par
/>\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers\par
<SidebarMenu>\par
  \{projects.map((project) => (\par
    <SidebarMenuItem key=\{project.name\}>\par
      <SidebarMenuButton asChild>\par
        <a href=\{project.url\}>\par
          <project.icon />\par
          <span>\{project.name\}</span>\par
        </a>\par
      </SidebarMenuButton>\par
    </SidebarMenuItem>\par
  ))\}\par
</SidebarMenu>\par
```\par
\par
## SidebarMenuButton\par
\par
The `SidebarMenuButton` component is used to render a menu button within a `SidebarMenuItem`.\par
\par
By default, the `SidebarMenuButton` renders a button but you can use the `asChild` prop to render a different component such as a `Link` or an `a` tag.\par
\par
Use the `isActive` prop to mark a menu item as active.\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers\par
<SidebarMenuButton asChild isActive>\par
  <a href="#">Home</a>\par
</SidebarMenuButton>\par
```\par
\par
## SidebarMenuAction\par
\par
The `SidebarMenuAction` component is used to render a menu action within a `SidebarMenuItem`.\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers\par
<SidebarMenuItem>\par
  <SidebarMenuButton asChild>\par
    <a href="#">\par
      <Home />\par
      <span>Home</span>\par
    </a>\par
  </SidebarMenuButton>\par
  <SidebarMenuAction>\par
    <Plus /> <span className="sr-only">Add Project</span>\par
  </SidebarMenuAction>\par
</SidebarMenuItem>\par
```\par
\par
## SidebarMenuSub\par
\par
The `SidebarMenuSub` component is used to render a submenu within a `SidebarMenu`.\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers\par
<SidebarMenuItem>\par
  <SidebarMenuButton />\par
  <SidebarMenuSub>\par
    <SidebarMenuSubItem>\par
      <SidebarMenuSubButton />\par
    </SidebarMenuSubItem>\par
  </SidebarMenuSub>\par
</SidebarMenuItem>\par
```\par
\par
## SidebarMenuBadge\par
\par
The `SidebarMenuBadge` component is used to render a badge within a `SidebarMenuItem`.\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers\par
<SidebarMenuItem>\par
  <SidebarMenuButton />\par
  <SidebarMenuBadge>24</SidebarMenuBadge>\par
</SidebarMenuItem>\par
```\par
\par
## SidebarMenuSkeleton\par
\par
The `SidebarMenuSkeleton` component is used to render a skeleton for a `SidebarMenu`.\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers\par
<SidebarMenu>\par
  \{Array.from(\{ length: 5 \}).map((_, index) => (\par
    <SidebarMenuItem key=\{index\}>\par
      <SidebarMenuSkeleton />\par
    </SidebarMenuItem>\par
  ))\}\par
</SidebarMenu>\par
```\par
\par
## SidebarTrigger\par
\par
Use the `SidebarTrigger` component to render a button that toggles the sidebar.\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers\par
import \{ useSidebar \} from "@/components/ui/sidebar"\par
\par
export function CustomTrigger() \{\par
  const \{ toggleSidebar \} = useSidebar()\par
\par
  return <button onClick=\{toggleSidebar\}>Toggle Sidebar</button>\par
\}\par
```\par
\par
## SidebarRail\par
\par
The `SidebarRail` component is used to render a rail within a `Sidebar`. This rail can be used to toggle the sidebar.\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers\par
<Sidebar>\par
  <SidebarHeader />\par
  <SidebarContent>\par
    <SidebarGroup />\par
  </SidebarContent>\par
  <SidebarFooter />\par
  <SidebarRail />\par
</Sidebar>\par
```\par
\par
## Controlled Sidebar\par
\par
Use the `open` and `onOpenChange` props to control the sidebar.\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers\par
export function AppSidebar() \{\par
  const [open, setOpen] = React.useState(false)\par
\par
  return (\par
    <SidebarProvider open=\{open\} onOpenChange=\{setOpen\}>\par
      <Sidebar />\par
    </SidebarProvider>\par
  )\par
\}\par
```\par
\par
## Theming\par
\par
We use the following CSS variables to theme the sidebar.\par
\par
```css\par
@layer base \{\par
  :root \{\par
    --sidebar-background: 0 0% 98%;\par
    --sidebar-foreground: 240 5.3% 26.1%;\par
    --sidebar-primary: 240 5.9% 10%;\par
    --sidebar-primary-foreground: 0 0% 98%;\par
    --sidebar-accent: 240 4.8% 95.9%;\par
    --sidebar-accent-foreground: 240 5.9% 10%;\par
    --sidebar-border: 220 13% 91%;\par
    --sidebar-ring: 217.2 91.2% 59.8%;\par
  \}\par
\par
  .dark \{\par
    --sidebar-background: 240 5.9% 10%;\par
    --sidebar-foreground: 240 4.8% 95.9%;\par
    --sidebar-primary: 0 0% 98%;\par
    --sidebar-primary-foreground: 240 5.9% 10%;\par
    --sidebar-accent: 240 3.7% 15.9%;\par
    --sidebar-accent-foreground: 240 4.8% 95.9%;\par
    --sidebar-border: 240 3.7% 15.9%;\par
    --sidebar-ring: 217.2 91.2% 59.8%;\par
  \}\par
\}\par
```\par
