## Changelog\par
\par
### RTL Support\par
\par
If you're upgrading from a previous version of the `Sidebar` component, you'll need to apply the following updates to add RTL support:\par
\par
<Steps>\par
\par
<Step>Add `dir` prop to Sidebar component.</Step>\par
\par
Add `dir` to the destructured props and pass it to `SheetContent` for mobile:\par
\par
```diff\par
  function Sidebar(\{\par
    side = "left",\par
    variant = "sidebar",\par
    collapsible = "offcanvas",\par
    className,\par
    children,\par
+   dir,\par
    ...props\par
  \}: React.ComponentProps<"div"> & \{\par
    side?: "left" | "right"\par
    variant?: "sidebar" | "floating" | "inset"\par
    collapsible?: "offcanvas" | "icon" | "none"\par
  \}) \{\par
```\par
\par
Then pass it to `SheetContent` in the mobile view:\par
\par
```diff\par
  <Sheet open=\{openMobile\} onOpenChange=\{setOpenMobile\} \{...props\}>\par
    <SheetContent\par
+     dir=\{dir\}\par
      data-sidebar="sidebar"\par
      data-slot="sidebar"\par
      data-mobile="true"\par
```\par
\par
<Step>Add `data-side` attribute to sidebar container.</Step>\par
\par
Add `data-side=\{side\}` to the sidebar container element:\par
\par
```diff\par
  <div\par
    data-slot="sidebar-container"\par
+   data-side=\{side\}\par
    className=\{cn(\par
```\par
\par
<Step>Update sidebar container positioning classes.</Step>\par
\par
Replace JavaScript ternary conditional classes with CSS data attribute selectors:\par
\par
```diff\par
  className=\{cn(\par
-   "fixed inset-y-0 z-10 hidden h-svh w-(--sidebar-width) transition-[left,right,width] duration-200 ease-linear md:flex",\par
-   side === "left"\par
-     ? "left-0 group-data-[collapsible=offcanvas]:left-[calc(var(--sidebar-width)*-1)]"\par
-     : "right-0 group-data-[collapsible=offcanvas]:right-[calc(var(--sidebar-width)*-1)]",\par
+   "fixed inset-y-0 z-10 hidden h-svh w-(--sidebar-width) transition-[left,right,width] duration-200 ease-linear md:flex data-[side=left]:left-0 data-[side=right]:right-0 data-[side=left]:group-data-[collapsible=offcanvas]:left-[calc(var(--sidebar-width)*-1)] data-[side=right]:group-data-[collapsible=offcanvas]:right-[calc(var(--sidebar-width)*-1)]",\par
```\par
\par
<Step>Update SidebarRail positioning classes.</Step>\par
\par
Update the `SidebarRail` component to use physical positioning for the rail:\par
\par
```diff\par
  className=\{cn(\par
-   "hover:after:bg-sidebar-border absolute inset-y-0 z-20 hidden w-4 -translate-x-1/2 transition-all ease-linear group-data-[side=left]:-end-4 group-data-[side=right]:start-0 after:absolute after:inset-y-0 after:start-1/2 after:w-[2px] sm:flex",\par
+   "hover:after:bg-sidebar-border absolute inset-y-0 z-20 hidden w-4 ltr:-translate-x-1/2 rtl:-translate-x-1/2 transition-all ease-linear group-data-[side=left]:-right-4 group-data-[side=right]:left-0 after:absolute after:inset-y-0 after:start-1/2 after:w-[2px] sm:flex",\par
```\par
\par
<Step>Add RTL flip to SidebarTrigger icon.</Step>\par
\par
Add `className="rtl:rotate-180"` to the icon in `SidebarTrigger` to flip it in RTL mode:\par
\par
```diff\par
  <Button ...>\par
-   <PanelLeftIcon />\par
+   <PanelLeftIcon className="rtl:rotate-180" />\par
    <span className="sr-only">Toggle Sidebar</span>\par
  </Button>\par
```\par
\par
</Steps>\par
\par
After applying these changes, you can use the `dir` prop to set the direction:\par
\par
```tsx\par
<Sidebar dir="rtl" side="right">\par
  \{/* ... */\}\par
</Sidebar>\par
```\par
\par
The sidebar will correctly position itself and handle interactions in both LTR and RTL layouts.\f0\par
